## EMERGENCY STOP CONDITIONS

Stop immediately if:
- User hasn't given explicit permission
- You're about to make changes without confirmation
- You're not sure if you have permission
- The user seems uncertain about the changes

## VIOLATION PROTOCOL

If you accidentally make changes without permission:
1. IMMEDIATELY stop and apologize
2. Explain what you should have done instead
3. Ask if user wants you to revert the changes
4. Commit to following the protocol going forward

